dlinkSwIpMcastExtMIB.name: dlinkSwIpMcastExtMIB

revisions.description: Initial revision of this MIB module.

Modify 'dIpmcExtStaticMrouteTable ', 'dIpmcExtRpfTable',dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPortTable and 'dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPortTable'. Modify the description of objects in 'dIpmcExtIgmpIfStatTable', 'dIpmcExtPimIfStatTable', and 'dIpmcExtDvmrpIfStatTable'.
Modify the OID of all rowstatus objects to 99.

Remove objects IpmcExtStaticMrouteDistance and dIpmcExtRpfDistance because we don't have plan to implement these objects now. Add the description for setting the value of dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfAddr to zero.

dlinkSwIpMcastExtMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects for managing IP Multicast.

dIpmcExtMcastRouteEnabled.name: dIpmcExtMcastRouteEnabled
dIpmcExtMcastRouteEnabled.description: This object indicates whether the specific multicast routing is enabled. This is the enhancement of the ipMcastEnabled in IPMCAST-MIB. If ipv4(0) bit is set to 1, then IPv4 multicast routing is enabled; If ipv6(1) bit is set to 1, then IPv6 multicast routing is enabled.

dIpmcExtIpv4McastTableLookupMode.name: dIpmcExtIpv4McastTableLookupMode
dIpmcExtIpv4McastTableLookupMode.description: This object indicates the lookup mode of IPv4 multicast forwarding table. 'ip' - forwarding IP multicast packets based on IP. 'mac' - forwarding IP multicast packets based on MAC.

dIpmcExtClearStatistics.name: dIpmcExtClearStatistics
dIpmcExtClearStatistics.description: This object is used to clear the multicast protocol packet statistics when set to the corresponding bit to '1'. When read, '00'H (no enumerated values are set) is returned.

dIpmcExtBoundaryTable.name: dIpmcExtBoundaryTable
dIpmcExtBoundaryTable.description: The table contains a list of interface-specific configuration about access lists to avoid leaking of the limited scoped multicast traffic in private domain across the domain boundary interfaces.

dIpmcExtBoundaryEntry.name: dIpmcExtBoundaryEntry
dIpmcExtBoundaryEntry.description: An entry is used to avoid leaking of the limited scoped multicast traffic in private domain across the domain boundary interfaces.

dIpmcExtBoundaryVersion.name: dIpmcExtBoundaryVersion
dIpmcExtBoundaryVersion.description: This object indicates the IP protocol version of the entry.

dIpmcExtBoundaryIfIdx.name: dIpmcExtBoundaryIfIdx
dIpmcExtBoundaryIfIdx.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the entry. Only VLAN interface is valid.

dIpmcExtBoundaryAccessList.name: dIpmcExtBoundaryAccessList
dIpmcExtBoundaryAccessList.description: This object indicates the name of a standard IP access list which includes a list of permit or denied (*,G) or (S,G) entries.

dIpmcExtBoundaryApplyDirection.name: dIpmcExtBoundaryApplyDirection
dIpmcExtBoundaryApplyDirection.description: The filtering setting for inbound direction filters the multicast user traffic arriving at the interface based on the specified access list. The filtering setting for outbound direction filters the PIM join message or IGMP join message arrive at the interface based on the specified access list.

dIpmcExtBoundaryRowStatus.name: dIpmcExtBoundaryRowStatus
dIpmcExtBoundaryRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteTable.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteTable
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteTable.description: A table consists of a list of static multicast routes.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteEntry.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteEntry
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteEntry.description: An entry is used to configure a static multicast route.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetType.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetType
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetType.description: This object indicates the address type of the multicast source network.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetAddr.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetAddr
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetAddr.description: This object indicates the address of the multicast source network.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetPreLen.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetPreLen
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetPreLen.description: This object indicates the prefix length of the multicast source network.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfType.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfType
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfType.description: This object indicates the type of the RPF (Reverse Path Forwarding). neighborAddr - The RPF address for the route, a lookup in the routing table will be done to resolve the RPF interface. interfaceId - The interface which the reverse path forwarding to reach the network.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfAddr.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfAddr
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfAddr.description: This object indicates the address of the RPF neighbor router. This object is meaningful when dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfType is 'neighborAddr'. If the value of this obejct is set to zero, it indicates that RPF check will be always failed for multicast traffic sent from the source network specified by this static multicast route. The InetAddressType, e.g., IPv4 or IPv6, is identified by the dIpmcExtStaticMrouteSrcNetType variable in the dIpmcExtStaticMrouteTable table.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfIfIndex.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfIfIndex
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfIfIndex.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the interface where the RPF neighbor IP address is located. When set this object to ifIndex of null0, the RPF check result will always fail. This object is meaningful when dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRpfType is 'interfaceId'.

dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRowStatus.name: dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRowStatus
dIpmcExtStaticMrouteRowStatus.description: The status of this row, by which rows in this table can be created and destroyed.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterTable.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterTable
dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterTable.description: A table consists of a list of information to filter layer 3 control packets. An entry appears in this table for each interface on which the filtering is configurable.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterEntry.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterEntry
dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterEntry.description: An entry identifies the layer 3 control packets filtering on a capable interface.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterIfIdx.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterIfIdx
dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterIfIdx.description: The ifIndex value that uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterV4Proto.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterV4Proto
dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterV4Proto.description: This object indicates whether the IPv4 layer 3 control packets is filtered then not sent to the corresponding protocol stack. When the bit is '1', the corresponding IPv4 layer 3 control packets will be filtered.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterV6Proto.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterV6Proto
dIpmcExtCtrlPktCpuFilterV6Proto.description: This object indicates whether the IPv6 layer 3 control packets is filtered then not sent to the corresponding protocol stack. When the bit is '1', the corresponding IPv6 layer 3 control packets will be filtered.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktReplacePriTable.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktReplacePriTable
dIpmcExtCtrlPktReplacePriTable.description: A table consists of a list of Priority and DSCP values of control packets which are forwarded by software.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktReplacePriEntry.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktReplacePriEntry
dIpmcExtCtrlPktReplacePriEntry.description: An entry consists of the Priority and DSCP values configured for a protocol.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriPotocol.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriPotocol
dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriPotocol.description: This object indicates the protocol type of the entry.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepDscp.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepDscp
dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepDscp.description: This object indicates the DSCP value to replace the DSCP field of the protocol control packets. The value of -1 indicates the replacing DSCP is not enabled.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriority.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriority
dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriority.description: This object indicates the Priority value to replace the Priority field of the protocol control packets. The value of -1 indicates the replacing Priority is not enabled.

dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriRowStatus.name: dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriRowStatus
dIpmcExtCtrlPktRepPriRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dIpmcExtRpfTable.name: dIpmcExtRpfTable
dIpmcExtRpfTable.description: A table consists of Reverse Path Forwarding (RPF) information.

dIpmcExtRpfEntry.name: dIpmcExtRpfEntry
dIpmcExtRpfEntry.description: An entry consists of Reverse Path Forwarding (RPF) information.

dIpmcExtRpfAddrType.name: dIpmcExtRpfAddrType
dIpmcExtRpfAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of the RPF address.

dIpmcExtRpfAddr.name: dIpmcExtRpfAddr
dIpmcExtRpfAddr.description: This object indicates the RPF address of the entry.

dIpmcExtRpfRouteAddr.name: dIpmcExtRpfRouteAddr
dIpmcExtRpfRouteAddr.description: This object indicates the route that matched against the source. The InetAddressType, e.g., IPv4 or IPv6, is identified by the dIpmcExtRpfAddrType variable in the dIpmcExtRpfTable table.

dIpmcExtRpfRoutePrefixLen.name: dIpmcExtRpfRoutePrefixLen
dIpmcExtRpfRoutePrefixLen.description: This object indicates the prefix length of the route that matched against the source.

dIpmcExtRpfIfIndex.name: dIpmcExtRpfIfIndex
dIpmcExtRpfIfIndex.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the interface where the RPF neighbor IP address is located. A value of 0 indicates that this object is not applicable.

dIpmcExtRpfNeighborAddr.name: dIpmcExtRpfNeighborAddr
dIpmcExtRpfNeighborAddr.description: This object indicates the RPF neighbor address. The InetAddressType, e.g., IPv4 or IPv6, is identified by the dIpmcExtRpfAddrType variable in the dIpmcExtRpfTable table.

dIpmcExtRpfType.name: dIpmcExtRpfType
dIpmcExtRpfType.description: This object indicates the origination of RPF information.

dIpmcExtRpfMetricValid.name: dIpmcExtRpfMetricValid
dIpmcExtRpfMetricValid.description: This object indicates whether the dIpmcExtRpfMetric of the entry is applicable.

dIpmcExtRpfMetric.name: dIpmcExtRpfMetric
dIpmcExtRpfMetric.description: This object indicates the unicast routing metric.

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPortTable.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPortTable

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPortEntry.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPortEntry
dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPortEntry.description: An entry contains the information about outgoing port to which IP multicast datagrams from particular sources to an IP multicast group address.

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingAddrType.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingAddrType
dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingAddrType.description: A value indicating the address type of the group address

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingVlanIndex.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingVlanIndex
dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingVlanIndex.description: This indicates the VLAN ID of the entry.

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingGroupAddr.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingGroupAddr

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPfxLen.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPfxLen
dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPfxLen.description: The length in bits of the multicast group address.

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingSrcAddr.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingSrcAddr
dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingSrcAddr.description: A value indicating the source address. The InetAddressType, e.g., IPv4 or IPv6, is identified by the dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingAddrType variable in the dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPortTable table.

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingSrcPfxLen.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingSrcPfxLen

dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPort.name: dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPort
dIpmcExtGrpOutgoingPort.description: The ifIndex value of the outgpoing port.
